WEBVTT

00:12.280 --> 00:16.680
An unforgiving, sun-baked,
desert in southern Africa

00:16.720 --> 00:19.600
is a tough place
to raise a family.

00:19.640 --> 00:20.800
[THUNDER CLAPS]

00:23.720 --> 00:25.680
But there are some...

00:25.720 --> 00:28.440
...who are perfectly suited
to it.

00:28.480 --> 00:31.360
[MUSIC]

00:31.400 --> 00:35.320
At the turn of the millennium
a legend was born here.

00:36.320 --> 00:39.680
Scientists named her Flower.

00:41.560 --> 00:44.720
As matriarch,
she grew her family...

00:46.160 --> 00:49.120
...leading them
through good times...

00:49.160 --> 00:50.720
and bad...

00:50.760 --> 00:52.760
[MEERKATS SQUAWK]

00:54.440 --> 00:58.880
...to become the most
successful leader of her kind,

00:58.920 --> 01:01.320
loved the world over.

01:05.360 --> 01:08.240
Like all living things,
when her time was done,

01:08.280 --> 01:11.040
the desert's rose
returned to the earth.

01:13.560 --> 01:16.960
But every great leader
leaves a legacy...

01:17.000 --> 01:21.960
And now the time has come
to pick up the story...

01:22.000 --> 01:24.320
with her great-granddaughters...

01:26.920 --> 01:29.400
as they strive
to lead their own families

01:29.440 --> 01:34.720
through the daily struggles of
life in the Kalahari.

01:36.320 --> 01:39.280
[MUSIC]

01:50.280 --> 01:51.280
[MEERKAT BARKS]

01:52.560 --> 01:54.040
[THUNDER CLAPS]

01:56.240 --> 01:58.040
[RAIN PATTERS]

02:22.280 --> 02:24.080
[MUSIC]

02:42.040 --> 02:46.840
The rising sun takes the chill
off a cold Kalahari night.

02:47.440 --> 02:49.560
[BIRDS CHIRP]

02:49.600 --> 02:51.400
Mornings are full of promise...

02:51.440 --> 02:54.400
and the Whiskers are gearing up
to start a new day.

02:54.440 --> 02:55.920
[MEERKATS SQUEAK]

03:06.680 --> 03:10.240
This has been the Whiskers' home
for more than twenty years.

03:12.600 --> 03:15.160
Swift is now head of the family,

03:15.200 --> 03:17.360
and like all dominant females
here,

03:17.400 --> 03:21.040
wears a radio collar
as her crown.

03:30.960 --> 03:33.160
To lead is to serve,

03:38.920 --> 03:42.680
and this steadfast leader
has served her family well

03:42.720 --> 03:44.480
for the past five years.

03:48.520 --> 03:50.960
Life hasn't always been easy.

03:51.000 --> 03:55.840
The Great Drought of 2015
almost wiped out the Whiskers.

03:58.240 --> 04:01.040
There were just three survivors

04:03.000 --> 04:04.520
but, from the devastation,

04:04.560 --> 04:07.160
Swift set about rebuilding
the dynasty -

04:07.200 --> 04:09.640
just as her great-grandmother
Flower did

04:09.680 --> 04:11.600
three generations before her.

04:15.200 --> 04:19.400
The Whiskers now number
a respectable fifteen.

04:26.320 --> 04:28.920
As matriarch, it's Swift's duty

04:28.960 --> 04:32.360
to ensure her family
keeps growing...

04:32.400 --> 04:36.920
...and three weeks ago, she gave
birth to her thirteenth litter!

04:39.160 --> 04:40.800
[BABY MEERKATS SQUEAK]

04:40.840 --> 04:42.440
Triplets!

04:43.560 --> 04:45.400
[BABY MEERKATS SQUAWK]

04:49.360 --> 04:54.120
Hachi, Laika... and Fly

04:54.160 --> 04:56.520
have been kept safely
underground

04:56.560 --> 05:00.880
and today they're seeing
daylight for the first time.

05:03.480 --> 05:05.040
[MEERKATS SQUAWK]

05:06.520 --> 05:08.840
[BIRDS SING]

05:20.840 --> 05:23.040
It's Swift's job to produce pups

05:23.080 --> 05:24.800
but it will be the
responsibility

05:24.840 --> 05:27.000
of the whole family
to raise them.

05:31.200 --> 05:33.800
All three are female...
which means

05:33.840 --> 05:37.080
there could be a feisty future
leader amongst them.

05:39.880 --> 05:44.120
Swift must balance motherhood
with her other duties as leader.

05:46.400 --> 05:48.680
Still too young
to leave the burrow,

05:48.720 --> 05:52.920
the pups will stay home
with a trusted babysitter.

05:52.960 --> 05:58.000
Today, that job falls to one of
Swift's four eldest daughters,

05:58.880 --> 06:01.720
Epsilon.

06:01.760 --> 06:05.120
This working mum can now lead
the rest of her family out

06:05.160 --> 06:06.800
to find food ...

06:06.840 --> 06:09.200
She'll be back just before
sunset

06:09.240 --> 06:12.000
to give the triplets
their bedtime milk.

06:17.440 --> 06:19.080
Swift has set
the Whiskers up

06:19.120 --> 06:23.440
in some of the best
real estate around.

06:23.480 --> 06:27.480
Their two square mile territory
hardly looks like a desert.

06:32.080 --> 06:34.720
Unusually high rainfall
in this spot,

06:34.760 --> 06:40.000
encourages all sorts of
delicacies to the surface.

06:40.040 --> 06:42.920
But you've got to be quick and
dextrous to catch them!

07:04.520 --> 07:06.760
[MUNCHING]

07:15.920 --> 07:20.040
Less than a mile from the ample
greenery of Chez Whiskers

07:20.080 --> 07:23.960
lies the smaller territory of
their nearest neighbours...

07:25.680 --> 07:27.360
...Hakuna Matata.

07:32.440 --> 07:37.440
It means no worries
but this family's got plenty.

07:41.360 --> 07:44.920
Their dry scrubland stands in
stark contrast

07:44.960 --> 07:47.320
to Swift's bountiful paradise.

07:51.480 --> 07:55.840
Finding nutritious meals
in this dust bowl is hard work.

07:59.040 --> 08:02.760
And compared with Swift,
the leader of this family...

08:02.800 --> 08:04.320
is a rookie.

08:04.360 --> 08:06.360
[SCRATCHING]

08:09.160 --> 08:11.240
Three-year-old, Flint Lockwood,

08:11.280 --> 08:15.800
has been in charge of Hakuna
Matata for less than a year.

08:15.840 --> 08:18.080
She too is descended
from Flower,

08:18.120 --> 08:20.720
as Flint is the great-great
grand-daughter

08:20.760 --> 08:23.040
of the Kalahari's
favourite rose.

08:26.080 --> 08:28.520
With a gang of ten,
mostly younger,

08:28.560 --> 08:30.280
siblings under her command,

08:30.320 --> 08:33.000
this beginner
has her hands full.

08:38.560 --> 08:43.600
Six weeks ago, Flint gave birth
to her first litter as leader.

08:43.640 --> 08:45.840
[MEERKATS CHATTER]

08:49.000 --> 08:52.720
Her three girls and one boy
are pretty demanding...

08:54.320 --> 08:55.680
...but this morning

08:55.720 --> 08:59.000
she's got a more immediate
problem to deal with.

09:00.520 --> 09:02.320
[ALARM CALL]

09:09.440 --> 09:11.760
Her partner Finnick's
head-bobbing

09:11.800 --> 09:13.800
signals he's concerned
about something.

09:18.640 --> 09:21.200
Until they know how serious
the problem is,

09:21.240 --> 09:24.560
it's best to gather the pups
together out of harm's way.

09:38.880 --> 09:40.920
As the search team spreads out,

09:40.960 --> 09:44.520
Flint's younger sister Sencha
stumbles into trouble.

09:48.480 --> 09:49.560
[BARKS]

09:55.240 --> 09:58.800
A sand snake is not
the deadliest predator

09:58.840 --> 10:00.440
but it's enough to raise
an alarm...

10:10.680 --> 10:12.160
[MEERKAT BARKS]

10:14.560 --> 10:16.880
The word is out.

10:16.920 --> 10:18.960
Flint's other sister, Munchkin,

10:19.000 --> 10:21.640
steps up to tackle the problem
head on.

10:24.520 --> 10:25.600
[BARKS]

10:25.640 --> 10:27.520
But snake-mobbing is
best attempted

10:27.560 --> 10:29.160
with a support team.

10:31.560 --> 10:35.360
Tails up to make themselves look
bigger, they crowd the snake -

10:35.400 --> 10:38.560
heads bobbing and spit-calling
in an attempt to force it away.

10:43.480 --> 10:44.720
[BARKS]

10:51.880 --> 10:53.880
Outnumbered and overwhelmed,

10:53.920 --> 10:56.800
the intruder turns tail
and slinks off.

11:04.440 --> 11:06.120
Flint could do without
all this stress

11:06.160 --> 11:07.720
first thing in the morning.

11:09.280 --> 11:12.480
But at least everyone's safe
for now.

11:24.600 --> 11:27.160
The differing fortunes of
Flower's descendants

11:27.200 --> 11:29.360
may simply be down to chance.

11:32.920 --> 11:34.880
As the temperature rises,

11:34.920 --> 11:39.400
Swift allows her now well-fed
family a welcome midday break.

11:45.800 --> 11:47.720
[SQUEAKS]

11:50.680 --> 11:53.600
Supervising playtime
in the shade

11:53.640 --> 11:57.920
is her long-term partner and
father to all the kids, Brea.

11:59.360 --> 12:03.560
At ten years old,
he's knocking on a bit

12:03.600 --> 12:06.000
although he still likes to
join in the fun...

12:06.040 --> 12:08.360
in a sedate kind of way.

12:11.440 --> 12:15.440
Swift's partnership with Brea
is full of affection

12:15.480 --> 12:17.640
and has lasted longer than most.

12:18.760 --> 12:21.880
Five glorious years together.

12:29.400 --> 12:33.040
As everyone gets back to the
grubby business of bug-hunting,

12:33.080 --> 12:36.400
oldest son Lilac takes up
look-out duty.

12:38.920 --> 12:40.960
Like young men the world over,

12:41.000 --> 12:43.240
Lilac has been slow
to leave home.

12:43.280 --> 12:46.880
But today the
snaggle-toothed man child

12:46.920 --> 12:50.400
is ready to answer
the call of the wild'.

12:55.600 --> 12:57.680
[FUNKY MUSIC]

12:58.600 --> 13:00.160
While no one's looking,

13:00.200 --> 13:04.560
this would-be Romeo sneaks off
in a different direction.

13:12.920 --> 13:17.080
Roving is the destiny
of every young male.

13:17.120 --> 13:20.280
It's the desert equivalent
of dating.

13:27.840 --> 13:31.240
But to find love in the dunes,
the inexperienced rover

13:31.280 --> 13:35.400
will have to venture
into enemy territory...

13:35.440 --> 13:39.960
and if rival males catch him
there, he'll be dead meat.

13:48.920 --> 13:53.520
Transition Desert dating doesn't
always end in disaster though.

13:53.560 --> 13:57.720
It's how Hakuna Matata's leader
Flint found her new man...

13:57.760 --> 14:00.000
or rather, he found her.

14:02.800 --> 14:06.000
Social climber Finnick
came looking for love'

14:06.040 --> 14:09.520
from a rival family
a few months ago.

14:09.560 --> 14:12.760
He spotted the vacancy
for dominant male,

14:12.800 --> 14:16.280
moved in, fathered Flint's pups

14:16.320 --> 14:18.840
and has been liberally swiping
his scent gland

14:18.880 --> 14:21.760
over his new patch ever since.

14:29.200 --> 14:30.560
Pups with Finnick

14:30.600 --> 14:32.920
have helped secure Flint's
position at the top

14:32.960 --> 14:35.600
but they've also exposed
a weakness.

14:36.480 --> 14:38.160
[SQUAWKING]

14:41.080 --> 14:42.800
A successful family

14:42.840 --> 14:46.520
is a finely-tuned
childcare machine...

14:46.560 --> 14:49.920
that runs mostly on girl power.

14:51.320 --> 14:54.040
Females without their own pups
can produce milk

14:54.080 --> 14:56.440
to help feed other members
of the family.

14:58.240 --> 15:01.920
But willing wet nurses
are in short supply.

15:05.400 --> 15:08.720
Finnick can't help...
even if he wanted to.

15:08.760 --> 15:10.240
Nor Shandy.

15:12.480 --> 15:15.400
Luther couldn't lactate
if his life depended on it.

15:16.680 --> 15:18.560
And Israel's all man.

15:20.680 --> 15:22.000
Gurke.

15:22.040 --> 15:23.920
Sacre Bleu.

15:23.960 --> 15:26.080
Belphagor...

15:26.120 --> 15:29.240
Man alive!
It's a desert boy's club.

15:35.120 --> 15:38.680
Unlike Swift, Flint doesn't have
an army of able daughters

15:38.720 --> 15:40.680
under her control.

15:46.280 --> 15:50.800
Her most senior deputy
is younger sister Munchkin.

15:51.960 --> 15:53.680
But Munchkin's blossoming

15:53.720 --> 15:56.960
into the kind of Kalahari
heart-stopper

15:57.000 --> 16:00.520
that's catnip to roving males.

16:00.560 --> 16:03.560
And right now, she's more
interested in boys

16:03.600 --> 16:05.640
than in looking after the kids.

16:11.320 --> 16:13.360
With little in the way
of child support

16:13.400 --> 16:16.760
and the constant pressure
to keep her family fed,

16:16.800 --> 16:19.560
it's no wonder Flint
is exhausted...

16:20.960 --> 16:22.480
...and fractious.

16:24.520 --> 16:26.480
And Munchkin...

16:26.520 --> 16:28.080
...takes the brunt of it.

16:32.280 --> 16:37.480
Watching Flint's family from
afar is rookie rover, Lilac.

16:37.520 --> 16:39.200
He's reached enemy territory

16:39.240 --> 16:41.560
but he's less interested
in the danger

16:41.600 --> 16:45.800
and more attracted to the oasis
of romantic promise!

16:52.000 --> 16:55.200
This could be his lucky day.

16:59.760 --> 17:02.040
The charming Ms. Munchkin...

17:03.880 --> 17:06.880
...and her equally delightful
sister Sencha

17:06.920 --> 17:10.320
might invite the attention
of an ambitious young rover.

17:17.600 --> 17:19.680
But...Oh...
Wait...

17:22.560 --> 17:26.120
a battalion of boys stands
between Lilac and the ladies.

17:33.920 --> 17:37.520
If they or Finnick spot him
there'll be serious trouble.

17:42.160 --> 17:44.480
Time to try
a different approach then.

17:47.960 --> 17:50.880
Perhaps they've left a
babysitter at their burrow.

17:53.240 --> 17:55.520
But...the burrow is deserted.

18:02.720 --> 18:06.720
Ah well, good things come
to he who waits.

18:22.000 --> 18:23.600
Back at the Whisker's burrow,

18:23.640 --> 18:27.000
Epsilon would be the perfect
catch for any rover.

18:27.040 --> 18:28.920
[MEERKAT SQUAWKS]

18:28.960 --> 18:31.960
...although at the moment
she's got her hands full

18:32.000 --> 18:33.800
looking after her baby sisters.

18:36.280 --> 18:39.560
While they explore
the wonders of the outdoors,

18:44.240 --> 18:46.920
she keeps a watchful eye out
for trouble.

18:48.800 --> 18:53.040
But four hours of this
would test anyone's patience.

18:55.960 --> 18:57.680
[MEERKAT SQUAWKS]

18:57.720 --> 19:00.480
Fortunately for Epsilon,
help is at hand.

19:01.760 --> 19:04.120
Her sisters Pandi...

19:04.160 --> 19:06.120
and Crimson
have returned home early

19:06.160 --> 19:08.040
to help with the childcare.

19:10.440 --> 19:12.320
It's a blessed relief.

19:18.080 --> 19:21.080
[SQUEAKS]

19:21.120 --> 19:23.880
All this playing
is thirsty work.

19:26.040 --> 19:27.560
Mum won't be back
for a few hours

19:27.600 --> 19:30.600
so big sister Crimson provides.

19:39.680 --> 19:44.240
And when feeding time is over,
everyone can enjoy forty winks.

19:56.800 --> 20:01.560
On Flint's side of the Manor,
there's been no time to rest.

20:01.600 --> 20:05.040
After a difficult day trying to
find enough food for everyone,

20:05.080 --> 20:07.920
she's finally
taking her family home.

20:09.680 --> 20:12.040
[LOUD SQUARKS]

20:12.080 --> 20:14.520
But their journey
is rudely interrupted.

20:15.680 --> 20:16.800
[LOUD SQUARKS]

20:16.840 --> 20:19.040
The Manor's
noisiest neighbours -

20:19.080 --> 20:21.080
a pair of
ground-nesting plovers -

20:21.120 --> 20:23.480
have got themselves
in quite a flap.

20:26.000 --> 20:30.080
[LOUD SQUARKS]

20:30.120 --> 20:31.680
The Hakuna Matata clan

20:31.720 --> 20:35.280
has stumbled
onto their nesting site.

20:35.320 --> 20:37.240
Their cunningly camouflaged eggs

20:37.280 --> 20:40.960
would be a delicious afternoon
snack for the hungry clan...

20:41.000 --> 20:43.000
If only they
could get to them...

20:47.320 --> 20:50.560
...but the birds
aren't about to allow that.

20:50.600 --> 20:52.600
[LOUD SQUARKS]

21:11.160 --> 21:14.200
Flint decides
it's not worth all the bother.

21:14.240 --> 21:16.720
It's been quite a day of
unpleasant surprises

21:16.760 --> 21:18.760
and she just wants to get home.

21:26.040 --> 21:29.560
The commotion alerts
rover-in-waiting Lilac

21:29.600 --> 21:32.280
to the rival family's
imminent return.

21:34.960 --> 21:38.680
The hapless Romeo makes his
escape while he still can.

21:42.360 --> 21:44.720
Roving is all about timing...

21:44.760 --> 21:49.040
And Lilac's lucky timing
may have just saved his life.

21:51.080 --> 21:54.480
Finnick immediately
smells a rat!!!

21:54.520 --> 21:58.080
He knows full well there's been
an intruder at his burrow!

22:00.240 --> 22:03.640
But Lilac is already
crossing safely back

22:03.680 --> 22:05.000
into Whiskers territory.

22:10.720 --> 22:13.640
[CALM MUSIC]

22:15.720 --> 22:18.960
As the sun begins
to set on the day,

22:19.000 --> 22:22.680
the rest of Lilac's family
are making their way home too.

22:23.560 --> 22:25.080
Swift leads the way.

22:27.200 --> 22:29.400
After a long day
apart from her pups

22:29.440 --> 22:31.880
she's keen to check on
their well-being.

22:35.280 --> 22:38.320
She has no cause for concern.

22:38.360 --> 22:39.720
Her able and willing daughters

22:39.760 --> 22:43.040
have played their babysitting
roles perfectly.

22:45.680 --> 22:47.760
Hachi, Laika and Fly

22:47.800 --> 22:52.160
have safely spent
their first day above ground.

22:53.840 --> 22:56.360
[MEERKATS SQUAWK]

22:58.960 --> 23:01.560
Pushy little Hachi
wastes no time

23:01.600 --> 23:05.200
securing the first bedtime
feed from her mum.

23:09.160 --> 23:11.200
As the African proverb goes -

23:11.240 --> 23:15.520
it takes a village
to raise a child.

23:15.560 --> 23:19.120
And the Whiskers
are making a fine job of it.

23:22.480 --> 23:24.360
Life will be full of challenges

23:24.400 --> 23:27.400
for the youngest members
of the Whiskers dynasty.

23:28.840 --> 23:31.640
But nobody would
expect those challenges

23:31.680 --> 23:34.960
to come quite so soon...

23:40.520 --> 23:43.520
♪

23:43.560 --> 23:45.880
Narrator:
Home is where the heart is.

23:45.920 --> 23:47.880
Sometimes your only choice

23:47.920 --> 23:49.520
is to move on.

23:49.560 --> 23:51.480
It's time for
the youngest members

23:51.520 --> 23:54.720
to experience life
beyond the burrow.

23:54.760 --> 23:56.400
Everybody is itching to get out.

23:56.440 --> 23:58.040
[Chirping]

23:58.080 --> 24:02.000
Across the manor, another mother
is leading her family.

24:02.040 --> 24:05.320
The stakes are high for
this inexperienced leader.

24:05.360 --> 24:06.360
[Chirp]

24:06.400 --> 24:09.120
♪

24:10.640 --> 24:13.160
[MUSIC]
